Compute maintainability metrics for source code in many languages.

big-code-analysis is a tree-sitter-based Rust library and command-line
tool that extracts metrics — cognitive complexity, cyclomatic, Halstead,
LOC, maintainability index, ABC, exit points, and more — from source
code in C, C++, JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, Java, C#, Go, Kotlin,
Rust, Bash, Lua, Perl, PHP, and Tcl.

Two binaries are installed:
  bca       - CLI for analysing files or trees and emitting
              JSON/YAML/TOML/CBOR reports.
  bca-web   - REST API server that wraps the same library for HTTP
              callers.
